AQA A-Level Politics (7152) – Core Specification (Simplified)
1. Course Structure
3 Papers (all 2 hours, 77 marks each)
Paper 1: UK Government & Politics
Paper 2: USA Government & Comparative Politics
Paper 3: Political Ideas
2. Exam Skills (VERY IMPORTANT)

You must be able to:

AO1: Knowledge (facts, definitions, examples)
AO2: Analysis (explain, compare, link)
AO3: Evaluation (arguments, judgement, conclusions)
Question types:
9 markers: 3 developed points (clear + examples)
25 markers (extract): balanced analysis + evaluation
25 markers (essay): sustained argument + judgement
